label.value: granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor receptor subunit alpha isoform 2 (mouse)

value.value: A granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor receptor subunit alpha (mouse) that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:A9P557. This isoform lacks part of the Fibronectin type-III (PS50853) domain.

definition.value: Category=organism-sequence. Evidence=(ECO:0000006, based on PMID:17694571, at protein level). Note: PMID:17694571 shows that this isoform may be produced from a transcript where skipping of the splice acceptor of exon 6 and aberrant splicing into the coding sequence of exon 6 occurs.
